  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Qt crash: “fatal internal error” / <code>hashMerkleRoot mismatch</code> on first run?</strong>
    Bloodstone Core Qt <strong>v0.7.0</strong> shipped a broken genesis block — fresh installs fail immediately. Fixed in <strong>v0.7.1</strong>.
    <ul class="compact">
      <li>Download <a href="bloodstone-qt-0.7.1-win64.exe">bloodstone-qt-0.7.1-win64.exe</a> (confirm <code>debug.log</code> says <code>Bloodstone version v0.7.1</code>).</li>
      <li>Reset chain data left by a failed v0.7.0 run — wallets are kept: <a href="reset-bloodstone-chain-data.ps1">reset-bloodstone-chain-data.ps1</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Qt wallet shows “Incorrect or no genesis block” / wrong datadir?</strong>
    That means old pre-relaunch chain data is still on disk (often under <code>%APPDATA%\Bloodstone</code> or <code>%APPDATA%\SpaceXpanse</code>).
    Your coins stay in <code>wallets/</code> — only <code>blocks/</code> and <code>chainstate/</code> need to go.
    <ul class="compact">
      <li><strong>Directory does not exist?</strong> download <a href="fix-bloodstone-qt-datadir.ps1">fix-bloodstone-qt-datadir.ps1</a> (removes bad <code>datadir=</code> lines), or <a href="reset-bloodstone-chain-data.ps1">reset-bloodstone-chain-data.ps1</a> for old chain data.</li>
      <li><strong>Better fix:</strong> install <a href="bloodstone-qt-0.7.1-win64.exe">bloodstone-qt v0.7.1</a> — it detects old data on startup and offers a one-click reset (keeps wallets).</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Looking for the core Qt wallet?</strong>
    The official Bitcoin-style GUI is <code>bloodstone-qt</code> (Bloodstone Core Qt).
    <ul class="compact">
      <li><strong>Linux:</strong> included in the wallet package below — run <code>bin/bloodstone-qt</code> after extracting.</li>
      <li><strong>Windows:</strong> download <a href="bloodstone-qt-0.7.1-win64.exe">bloodstone-qt-0.7.1-win64.exe</a>
        (standalone) or use <code>bin/bloodstone-qt.exe</code> inside the
        <a href="bloodstone-wallet-0.7.1-win64.zip">full wallet zip</a>.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

