  <h2 id="lan-forwarder">LAN ASIC hashrate forwarder (Gamma + Lucky)</h2>
  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Pool dashboard shows ~10 MH/s instead of terahashes?</strong>
    The VPS cannot reach miners on your home LAN (<code>192.168.x.x</code>). Run the forwarder on any PC on the same Wi‑Fi/Ethernet as your miners — it polls Gamma (Bitaxe API) and Lucky (CGMiner API) and pushes real hashrate to the pool.
    <ul class="compact">
      <li><strong>Windows (one line):</strong> PowerShell → <code>Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope Process Bypass; irm https://bloodstonewallet.mytunnel.org/downloads/install-lan-miner-forwarder.ps1 | iex</code></li>
      <li><strong>Linux / Pi:</strong> <code>curl -fsSL https://bloodstonewallet.mytunnel.org/downloads/install-lan-miner-forwarder.sh | bash</code></li>
      <li><strong>Manual files:</strong> <a href="lan-miner-hashrate-forward.py">lan-miner-hashrate-forward.py</a> · <a href="lan-miner-devices.json">lan-miner-devices.json</a> · <a href="install-lan-miner-forwarder.ps1">install-lan-miner-forwarder.ps1</a> · <a href="install-lan-miner-forwarder.sh">install-lan-miner-forwarder.sh</a></li>
    </ul>
    Edit <code>lan-miner-devices.json</code> if Lucky’s IP is not auto-discovered (set <code>"host": "http://192.168.x.x"</code> instead of <code>auto</code>).
  </div>

  <p class="muted">SHA256 checksums: append <code>.sha256</code> to any filename (e.g. <code>bloodstone-node-0.7.0-linux-x86_64.tar.gz.sha256</code>).</p>
  <script>
  (function () {
    var RELEASE_RE = /\.(?:apk|tar\.gz|tgz|tar\.xz|zip|exe|deb|rpm|msi|dmg|7z|sha256|ps1|sh)(?:\?|$)/i;
    function androidCapacitor() {
      return window.Capacitor && window.Capacitor.getPlatform && window.Capacitor.getPlatform() === "android";
    }
    if (!androidCapacitor()) return;
    document.addEventListener("click", function (event) {
      var anchor = event.target && event.target.closest ? event.target.closest("a[href]") : null;
      if (!anchor) return;
      var href = anchor.getAttribute("href") || "";
      var fileUrl;
      try {
        fileUrl = new URL(href, window.location.href).href;
      } catch (err) {
        fileUrl = href;
      }
      if (!RELEASE_RE.test(fileUrl)) return;
      event.preventDefault();
      var pool = window.Capacitor.Plugins && window.Capacitor.Plugins.BloodstoneDevicePool;
      var method = /\.apk(?:\?|$)/i.test(fileUrl) ? "downloadAndInstallApk" : "downloadReleaseFile";
      var action = pool && pool[method]
        ? pool[method]({ url: fileUrl })
        : window.Capacitor.nativePromise("BloodstoneDevicePool", method, { url: fileUrl });
      Promise.resolve(action).catch(function () {
        try {
          window.open(fileUrl, "_system");
        } catch (e2) {
          window.location.href = fileUrl;
        }
      });
    }, true);
  })();
  </script>
